<h1>Problem 667 - 2014 Taiwan TST3 Quiz 3, P1</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 6</h2>
<p>Positive integers \(x_1, x_2, \dots, x_n\) (\(n \ge 4\)) are arranged in a circle such that each \(x_i\) divides the sum of the neighbors; that is\[\frac{x_{i-1}+x_{i+1}}{x_i} = k_i\]is an integer for each \(i\), where \(x_0 = x_n\), \(x_{n+1} = x_1\). Prove that\[2n \le k_1 + k_2 + \dots + k_n < 3n.\]</p>
